The paper discusses a generic and computer-actionable vocabulary for describing deep learning configurations, training procedures, and experiments. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), specifically neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) as a potential use-case for the ontology. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
